<h2 style="line-height: 2;">4 Ways to invest in gold</h2>
<p style="line-height: 2;">Now that you have a general outlook on the pros and cons of gold, the next point to ponder is how to invest in gold. Therefore, understanding the usual channels you can own or trade in gold is vital.</p>
<h3 style="line-height: 2;">1. Bullion</h3>
<p style="line-height: 2;">The oldest way to invest in physical gold is through bullion. People purchase gold bullion through online dealers like JM Bullion or APMEX. People also buy from face-to-face referrals, local dealers, collectors, and pawn shops. Due to the rudimentary way of owning gold in this way, investors need to find a willing seller and still ensure that the quantity required is available and that they can get a fair deal. You can always cross-check with spot prices to keep you from getting ripped off. It also requires a safe way to transport and store it, considering it is in the form of gold bars, gold coins, or jewelry.</p>
<h3 style="line-height: 2;">2. Consider ETFs that own gold</h3>
<p style="line-height: 2;">To skip the complexities of owning physical gold and the cost of storing it safely, you can consider buying into ETFs that deal in gold. <a href="/en/etf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Buy gold ETFs</a> from top indices across the globe. Some popular gold ETFs include SPDR Gold Trust and iShares Gold Trust. The ETFs that deal in gold provides you with more liquidity and convenience because investors are only issued shares of actual gold held by the trust. They are a good way to replicate the performance of gold on the market while only charging investors a small expense ratio.</p>
<p style="line-height: 2;"><span style="font-size: 11px; color: #000000;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" style="height: auto; max-width: 100%; width: 624px;" src="https://www.atfx.com/hubfs/ATFX-gold-ETF%20(1).webp" alt="what is gold etf" width="624" height="322" /></span></p>
<h3 style="line-height: 2;">3. Gold futures</h3>
<p style="line-height: 2;">Gold futures are a convenient and quick way to speculate on gold prices. Investors can simply speculate whether the prices will rise or fall. COMEX Gold Futures (GC) is the top-recognized benchmark for the gold futures contract. People can get tips, analyses, and track daily changes when published online. Regular traders even make orders in the comfort of their homes. Click here to <a href="/en/markets/commodities" target="_blank" rel="noopener">trade commodities</a>.</p>
<h3 style="line-height: 2;">4. Trade gold as a currency</h3>
<p style="line-height: 2;">XAUUSD is among the pairs that forex brokers offer today. Include gold pairs in your <a href="/en/markets/forex-trading" target="_blank" rel="noopener">forex trading</a> if you already know how it works. As a free tip, trading gold as a currency pair helps you kill two birds with one stone, as you can apply the same strategies as you would with currencies and stocks. Live charts also help you monitor price changes in real-time. A beginner can open a demo account and test different strategies to make money with gold price movement using a guide.</p>
<h2 style="line-height: 2;">So, Should you buy gold?</h2>
<p style="line-height: 2;">The advantages of investing in gold far outweigh the disadvantages involved. The selected investment vehicle depends on the preferred time frame (short-term or long-term) and preferred reasons to buy the gold. Owners who want a fall-back plan during a war or political crisis would prefer physical gold because it is not tied to the country’s financial system. If you prefer making short-term speculative trades, gold ETFs and gold futures will give you liquid solutions that take advantage of price volatility.</p>
